verbose_text: Briefly, 12 h following the precipitation of the thrombus, data from ELISA, reverse transcription-quantitative polymerase chain reaction analysis and confocal microscopy revealed that the levels of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha, interleukin (IL)-6, CX3C chemokine ligand 1 (CX3CL1), CX3C chemokine receptor 1 (CX3CR1) and nuclear factor-kappaB (NF-kappaB) in group M were increased, compared with those in group N (P < 0.01).
evidence: levels of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha, interleukin
